history.text: hi there
Hello! Alright, the movie is The Imitation game
What is the movie about?
Sounds like a fantasy
It's loosely based on the biography of Alan Turing. So Benedict Cumberbatch is being a British Cryptanalyyst, Alan Turing.
when did this take place?
He decrypted German Intelligence codes for the british government, during World War II
wow, so he played a major role in the war
It's pretty highly rated, Rotten tomatoes gives it a 91%.
sounds like it did really well
It did. It also has Keira Knightley in it.
so he worked in a team of other cryptanalyst?
Yes, the team decrypts the Enigma Machine, which nazis used for coded messages, which sounds weird
Like that sounds like a sci-fi thin, Enigma Machine.
he must of been well awarded at the end of the war for his efforts
I don't know that he was, I don't have that information. Maybe not though, as he was gay in a time period where that was not well liked.
He has a romantic crush on a friend from boarding school, but that guy dies of tuberculosis before Turing can confess his love.
you haven't seen it?
it definitely sounds like a fascinating movie with a good storyline
Yeah, I think so. The sad part is Turing realizes that they can't act on every single message, or they nazis will know that the code is broken.
It's a hard call.
sounds like a great movie
love the history aspect of it
It takes a few artistic liberties, but still a great watch. CinemaScore gave it an A+
sounds like a very solid choice then
thanks for your feedback
No problem!
is there anything else that i should know about the movie?
Hm, well, there is the scene where one person is a spy, and blackmails Turing from telling with the information that he's gay.
After the war, they make the cryptographers destroy their work, too. Sad.
ah, so he was gay in a tough time to be open about it
lots of lost information, but at least they put the topic out there, thanks again!
